{"title":"Trek Doubles Down on Gravel Racing w/ New Checkmate SLR, Updated Checkpoint SL","link":"https://bikerumor.com/trek-checkmate-slr-checkpoint-sl-gen-3/","date":1723734000000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild--1536x979.png\" width=\"1536\" height=\"979\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 9 in the wild\" /></p>\n<p>The all-new Trek Checkmate SLR and Checkpoint SL further solidify the Wisconsin brand’s commitment to the gravel arts. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’ve followed any of the <a href=\"https://www.lifetimegrandprix.com/\">LifeTime Grand Prix, </a>chances are you’ve seen the Trek Checkmate frame. Companies like Trek and the like no longer try to hide their new gear right before a big launch. Or we consumers are getting better at spotting them. Either way, it looks fast and a lot like the<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-madone-gen-8/\"> Madone Gen 8</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint-.png\"><img width=\"9504\" height=\"6336\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint-.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 9 paint\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint-.png 9504w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint--297x198.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint--1536x1024.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint--120x80.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint--768x512.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint--2048x1365.png 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint--800x533.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-paint--720x480.png 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Who could blame them</em></strong>? If you’re an athlete like <a href=\"https://racing.trekbikes.com/riders/driftless/russell-finsterwald\">Russell Finsterwald </a>(Trek-Driftless) and your bike sponsor just came out with a flyin’ new gravel race frame, would you want to wait until the late season to race it? My guess is no, and Trek feels the same way. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The one that did catch us by surprise is the all-new (design) Trek Checkpoint SL. The<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-aims-for-a-gravel-world-championship-with-race-focused-checkpoint-slr-plus-sl-and-alr-models/\"> Checkpoint </a>was the go-to gravel frame in the Trek lineup, but it now leans more toward adventure, and it can still lay down the power if need be. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, let’s meet the new Trek gravel race and adventure lineup.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-shredding.png\"><img width=\"4622\" height=\"3262\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-shredding.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 9 shredding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-shredding.png 4622w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-shredding-297x210.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-shredding-1536x1084.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-shredding-120x85.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-shredding-768x542.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-shredding-2048x1445.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek Checkmate SLR</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>For the new Checkmate, Trek threw the gauntlet down in the gravel. It’s the company’s first-ever dedicated gravel race bike (if you discount the Checkpoint SLR). The new Checkmate models are much lighter than the Checkpoint SLR and get some help from top-tier specs. <em>How much lighter, you ask? </em>How about a whole pound?</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild-.png\"><img width=\"8193\" height=\"5222\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild-.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 9 in the wild\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild-.png 8193w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild--297x189.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild--1536x979.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild--120x76.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild--768x490.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-in-the-wild--2048x1305.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>5 minutes and 54 seconds faster than Checkpoint SLR</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame takes inspiration (lots) from the new Madone Gen 8 and uses Trek’s new series 800 carbon. Like the Madone Gen 8, Trek employs Full System Foil aero tube shapes and an aero one-piece bar/stem. Plus, the Checkmate’s new Gravel Race geo puts riders in a more aggressive and efficient riding position. Reducing frontal area, getting more aero, and saving watts (sounds like the Madone Gen 8 right?). Trek claims these features help make Checkmate 5 minutes and 54 seconds faster than Checkpoint SLR on the 200-mile course at Unbound (at 200W). </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s the Max Tire Size? </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Some will be stoked, some will be bummed. The new Checkmate maxes out at 45mm tires and comes stock with 38mm tires. 45mm seems to be the top of what most (super serious) racers will use until they switch to a full-on mountain bike (with drop bars or not). Stay tuned if you’re looking for a bike that clears a larger tire. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-drive-train-.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-drive-train-.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 7 drive train\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-drive-train-.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-drive-train--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-drive-train--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-drive-train--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-drive-train--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-drive-train--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Let Talk Compatibility</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Checkmate uses an SRAM UDH derailleur hanger and is compatible (and comes with) with the new SRAM Red XPLR groupset <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sram-red-xplr-13-speed-groupset/\">(reviewed here). </a></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Is there any internal storage?</em></strong> No, if you’re looking for storage, read on. Trek designers decided the extra weight of the in-frame storage was too much and went all in for maximum lightweight gains.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Dropper compatible? </em></strong>That’s a negative, too; the CheckMate uses a D-shaped seatpost—a first for Trek, but as we mentioned above, stay tuned. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Bags?</em></strong> Yes, the new Checkmate is designed to work seamlessly with the Trek Adventure bags and top tube feeding bags. But that’s where the bags stop; since the Checkmate is a race frame, Trek omits the three-pack mounts and the bike-packing mounts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR7ABars-.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR7ABars-.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR7ABars\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR7ABars-.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR7ABars--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR7ABars--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR7ABars--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR7ABars--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR7ABars--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Aero One-piece Bar/Stem </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Checkmate features the same ultra-light and aero one-piece carbon bar/stem as the Madone Gen 8. The same piece has hoods that are 3cm narrower than the drops, so riders can choose between a more aero or more controlled position and enjoy more ergonomic comfort on the tops. We love this bar; it’s one of the most comfortable aero bars around, and it’s nice to see it on a gravel bike aimed at racing. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo-.png\"><img width=\"2008\" height=\"1254\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo-.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL Gen 4 geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo-.png 2008w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo--297x185.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo--1536x959.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo--120x75.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo--768x480.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek Checkmate SLR Geo </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-head-tube-.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-head-tube-.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 7 head tube\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-head-tube-.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-head-tube--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-head-tube--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-head-tube--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-head-tube--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-head-tube--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Trek Checkmate SLR  Models and Pricing </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-full-.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-full-.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 7 full\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-full-.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-full--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-full--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-full--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-full--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-7-full--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Checkmate SLR7 </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Checkmate SLR7 is the new gravel race machine’s base model. It arrives with a SRAM Force AXS XPLR 1X groupset and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-bontrager-aeolus-pro-3v-tlr-wheels-go-super-wide-crushes-gravel/\">Bontrager Aeolus Pro V3 </a>wheels. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Price: </strong>$8,300 </li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight:</strong> 17.86 lbs </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-with-bags-.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-with-bags-.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 9 with bags\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-with-bags-.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-with-bags--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-with-bags--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-with-bags--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-with-bags--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-with-bags--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Checkmate SLR9</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Checkmate SLR9 is the top-tier version of the Checkmate. It arrives with the new SRAM Red AXS XPLR 1X groupset and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bontrager-aeolus-rsl-37v-brings-ultra-lightweight-carbon-wheels-to-gravel-bikes-cyclocross/\">Bontrager Aeolus RSL wheels</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Price: </strong>$12,00</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight: </strong>16.65 lbs </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Checkmate SLR Frameset </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Price: </strong>$4,000</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight: </strong>1223g (ML frame only) 415g (fork only) </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em>*All weights are size ML bikes with Bontrager TLR sealant, no tubes. </em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-.png\"><img width=\"3000\" height=\"2250\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-.png\" alt=\"Trek Checkmate SLR 9\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9-.png 3000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Trek-Checkmate-SLR-9--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Customizable in Project One </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The best way to get Checkmate is through Project One for the perfect fit, parts, and color. Plus, the new <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/project-one/\">Project One ICON Raw Lithos </a>scheme brings earthen hues exclusively to Checkmate customers. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-no-bags-.png\"><img width=\"3000\" height=\"2250\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-no-bags-.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL7 Gen 4 no bags\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-no-bags-.png 3000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-no-bags--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-no-bags--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-no-bags--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-no-bags--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-no-bags--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Updated Trek Checkpoint SL Gen 3</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re looking for speed, exploration, and a little racing –  the new Checkpoint SL Gen 3 will be the ticket. The new design improves the previous model with increased comfort, storage capacity, and fit. Looking to deliver a multifaceted bike that can race and ride on any given weekend.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Checkpoint SL Gen 3 uses the ISO speed system and a traditional round seat post. So droppers are fair game for all sizes. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL6 Gen 4\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Packable and More Storage </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Checkpoint is more bike-packable than before. Like the Checkmate, it works with <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/adventure-bags/\">Trek’s all-new Adventure Bags</a>, including the top tube, frame, and the more aero-efficient triangle bag tucked out of the wind. Plus, it has mounts for front and rear racks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Checkpoint SL Gen 3’s new frame design has more room to fit taller bottles (<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-voda-34oz-water-bottle-seriously/\">like our favorite Voda 34 oz)</a> with bags and offers more internal storage in the downtube than before. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-more-storage-.png\"><img width=\"1080\" height=\"802\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-more-storage-.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint more storage\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-more-storage-.png 1080w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-more-storage--297x221.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-more-storage--120x89.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-more-storage--768x570.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Updated Frame Shaping </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Checkpoint SL Gen 3 features reimagined tube shapes and 500 Series OCLV Carbon that keeps things lightweight, snappy, and economical. Like the Checkmate, the Checkpoint gets the Madone Gen 8 makeover with some sculpted tubes. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Confidence Inspiring Details </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Checkpoint SL Gen 3 uses Trek’s “Gravel Endurance geometry” and has a higher and shorter reach that’s more comfortable and capable for all-day gravel rides. Riders get a GR Elite handlebar (SL 5 and 6) or a carbon GR Pro handlebar (SL 7). Both share a more comfortable drop shape and an increased flare of 6cm between hoods and drops for better control and confidence, especially on gravel.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-5-.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-5-.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL Gen 4 5\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-5-.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-5--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-5--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-5--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-5--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-5--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Tire clearance? </em></strong>50mm. The Checkpoint SL Gen 3 arrives with 42mm tires but can fit bigger. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>How about suspension? </em></strong>Yep! The new Checkpoint SL Gen3 is a suspension fork compatible with forks up to 40mm of travel. (Available in all sizes except XS)</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo-.png\"><img width=\"2008\" height=\"1254\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo-.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL Gen 4 geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo-.png 2008w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo--297x185.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo--1536x959.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo--120x75.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-geo--768x480.png 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek Checkpoint SL Gen 3 Geometry </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-AXS-.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-AXS-.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL Gen 4 AXS\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-AXS-.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-AXS--297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-AXS--1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-AXS--120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-AXS--768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL-Gen-4-AXS--2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Trek Checkpoint SL Gen 3 Models and Pricing </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL5-Gen-4.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL5-Gen-4.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL5 Gen 4\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL5-Gen-4.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL5-Gen-4-297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL5-Gen-4-1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL5-Gen-4-120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL5-Gen-4-768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL5-Gen-4-2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Treks Checkpoint SL 5 AXS</strong> has an SRAM Apex AXS 12-speed, Bontrager Paradigm wheels, and a Bontrager GR Elite handlebar. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Price: </strong>$3,200</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight:</strong> 20.95lbs </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL6 Gen 4\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL6-Gen-4-2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The Checkpoint SL 6 AXS </strong>comes equipped with SRAM Rival AXS 12 speed, Bontrager Paradigm wheels, and a Bontrager GR Elite handlebar.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> $4,000</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight: </strong>20.73lbs.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4.png\"><img width=\"4000\" height=\"3000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4.png\" alt=\"Checkpoint SL7 Gen 4\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4.png 4000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-297x223.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-1536x1152.png 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-120x90.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-768x576.png 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/Checkpoint-SL7-Gen-4-2048x1536.png 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>The Checkpoint SL 7 AXS</strong> comes with SRAM Force AXS XPLR 12-speed, Bontrager Elite V35 carbon wheels, and a Bontrager GR Pro carbon handlebar.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> $5,700</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight: </strong>19.85lbs.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Checkpoint SL Frameset</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Price:</strong> $2,400</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Weight: </strong>1385g (ML frame only) 536g (fork-only)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><em>*All weights are size ML bikes with Bontrager TLR sealant, no tubes. </em></li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Checkpoint SL Gen 3 and Checkmate SLR are available globally at select Trek retailers and online at<a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/gravel-bike-buyers-guide/\"> trekbikes.com</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-checkmate-slr-checkpoint-sl-gen-3/\">Trek Doubles Down on Gravel Racing w/ New Checkmate SLR, Updated Checkpoint SL </a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","